<p>This is where I got the information. Am I interpreting this wrong?</p>","post_number":3,"post_type":1,"posts_count":34,"updated_at":"2022-08-10T00:45:39.560Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":2,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":2,"reads":148,"readers_count":147,"score":44.6,"yours":false,"topic_id":414034,"topic_slug":"schedule-a-command-without-calling-initialize","display_username":"Elliot Scher","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"link_counts":[{"url":"https://www.chiefdelphi.com/uploads/default/original/3X/1/c/1c5e388d4a1d80440ccf870629328bbdd802900e.png","internal":true,"reflection":false,"clicks":0}],"read":true,"user_title":"","reply_to_user":{"id":50684,"username":"crueter","name":"","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/crueter/{size}/258043_2.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":49423,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"2815A (19-23) | 190M (23...)"},"post_url":"/t/schedule-a-command-without-calling-initialize/414034/3","custom_user_title":"2815A (19-23) | 190M (23...)","reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":true},{"id":3076462,"name":"","username":"crueter","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/crueter/{size}/258043_2.png","created_at":"2022-08-10T00:51:11.826Z","cooked":"<p>Read it over again and your interpretation seems correct. However I think what you’re looking for is a <code>SequentialCommandGroup</code>. This lets you run several commands in sequences or parallels (with the <code>parallel()</code> function) and seems to fit exactly with what you’re trying to do.</p>
<p>This is what we did (<a href="https://github.com/Team4028/2022-Season/blob/competition/src/main/java/frc/robot/commands/auton/FiveBallBackupAuton.java">five ball</a> for reference–<code>util.getPathPlannerSwerveControllerCommand()</code> is equivalent to a ramsete command).</p>","post_number":4,"post_type":1,"posts_count":34,"updated_at":"2022-08-10T00:51:11.826Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":3,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":1,"reads":144,"readers_count":143,"score":33.8,"yours":false,"topic_id":414034,"topic_slug":"schedule-a-command-without-calling-initialize","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"link_counts":[{"url":"https://github.com/Team4028/2022-Season/blob/competition/src/main/java/frc/robot/commands/auton/FiveBallBackupAuton.java","internal":false,"reflection":false,"clicks":3}],"read":true,"user_title":"","reply_to_user":{"id":49423,"username":"Gandagorn","name":"Elliot Scher","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/gandagorn/{size}/267112_2.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":50684,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"6032 | QDash"},"post_url":"/t/schedule-a-command-without-calling-initialize/414034/4","custom_user_title":"6032 | QDash","reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":true},{"id":3076463,"name":"Gavin Matthews","username":"bovlb","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/bovlb/{size}/167232_2.png","created_at":"2022-08-10T00:51:54.657Z","cooked":"<p>If you assemble the commands into a <a href="https://docs.wpilib.org/en/stable/docs/software/commandbased/command-groups.html#sequentialcommandgroup">SequentialCommandGroup</a> and then schedule the group, each command (after the first) will not be initialized until the preceding command has ended.</p>","post_number":5,"post_type":1,"posts_count":34,"updated_at":"2022-08-10T00:51:54.657Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":1,"reads":138,"readers_count":137,"score":37.6,"yours":false,"topic_id":414034,"topic_slug":"schedule-a-command-without-calling-initialize","display_username":"Gavin Matthews","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"link_counts":[{"url":"https://docs.wpilib.org/en/stable/docs/software/commandbased/command-groups.html#sequentialcommandgroup","internal":false,"reflection":false,"title":"Command Groups — FIRST Robotics Competition documentation","clicks":2}],"read":true,"user_title":"","bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":38743,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"Programming mentor, Team 2102, RI, CSA (he/him)"},"post_url":"/t/schedule-a-command-without-calling-initialize/414034/5","custom_user_title":"Programming mentor, Team 2102, RI, CSA (he/him)","reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":true},{"id":3076464,"name":"Elliot Scher","username":"Gandagorn","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chi