<p>Commands also generally shouldn’t be manually scheduled from other commands- there’s almost always a better way to do what you’re trying to do.</p>","post_number":12,"post_type":1,"posts_count":34,"updated_at":"2022-08-10T03:13:19.815Z","reply_count":2,"reply_to_post_number":10,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":1,"reads":98,"readers_count":97,"score":79.6,"yours":false,"topic_id":414034,"topic_slug":"schedule-a-command-without-calling-initialize","display_username":"Ryan Blue","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":2,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"","reply_to_user":{"id":49423,"username":"Gandagorn","name":"Elliot Scher","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/gandagorn/{size}/267112_2.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[{"id":2,"count":3}],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":29846,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"WPILib Dev | 1024 Mentor"},"post_url":"/t/schedule-a-command-without-calling-initialize/414034/12","custom_user_title":"WPILib Dev | 1024 Mentor","reactions":[{"id":"heart","type":"emoji","count":3}],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":3,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":true},{"id":3076477,"name":"","username":"crueter","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/crueter/{size}/258043_2.png","created_at":"2022-08-10T02:39:03.993Z","cooked":"<p>For the scenario of running several commands in sequence/parallel then Sequential/ParallelCommandGroup should be used… but if you mean to never call <code>.schedule()</code> then I agree</p>","post_number":13,"post_type":1,"posts_count":34,"updated_at":"2022-08-10T02:39:03.993Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":12,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":3,"reads":96,"readers_count":95,"score":49.2,"yours":false,"topic_id":414034,"topic_slug":"schedule-a-command-without-calling-initialize","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"","reply_to_user":{"id":29846,"username":"Ryan_Blue","name":"Ryan Blue","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/ryan_blue/{size}/174016_2.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[{"id":2,"count":1}],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":50684,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"6032 | QDash"},"post_url":"/t/schedule-a-command-without-calling-initialize/414034/13","custom_user_title":"6032 | QDash","reactions":[{"id":"heart","type":"emoji","count":1}],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":1,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":true},{"id":3076479,"name":"Elliot Scher","username":"Gandagorn","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/gandagorn/{size}/267112_2.png","created_at":"2022-08-10T02:44:35.101Z","cooked":"<p>why is it bad to schedule commands within other commands?</p>","post_number":14,"post_type":1,"posts_count":34,"updated_at":"2022-08-10T02:44:35.101Z","reply_count":2,"reply_to_post_number":12,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":2,"reads":93,"readers_count":92,"score":38.6,"yours":false,"topic_id":414034,"topic_slug":"schedule-a-command-without-calling-initialize","display_username":"Elliot Scher","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"","reply_to_user":{"id":29846,"username":"Ryan_Blue","name":"Ryan Blue","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/ryan_blue/{size}/174016_2.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":49423,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"2815A (19-23) | 190M (23...)"},"post_url":"/t/schedule-a-command-without-calling-initialize/414034/14","custom_user_title":"2815A (19-23) | 190M (23...)","reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":true},{"id":3076490,"name":"Gavin Matthews","username":"bovlb","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/bovlb/{size}/167232_2.png","created_at":"2022-08-10T04:58:58.288Z","cooked":"<p>It’s not that it won’t work, it’s just that it’s a bad pattern (an “anti-pattern”) because it’s working against the way things are intended to work.</p>
<p>There are four main ways that commands get scheduled:</p>
<ul>
<li>As the autonomous command returned by <code>getAutonomousCommand()</code> and scheduled by <code>autonomousInit()</code>. <a href="https://docs.wpilib.org/en/stable/docs/software/commandbased/structuring-command-based-project.html#robot">link</a>
</li>
<li>As the default command for a subsystem, set by <code>CommandScheduler.getInstance().setDefaultCommand</code>. <a href="https://docs.wpilib.org/en/stable/docs/software/commandbased/subsystems.html?highlight=default%20commands#setting-default-commands">link</a>
</li>
<li>As the command to run when a button is pressed on the driver station. <a href="https://docs.wpilib.org/en/stable/docs/software/commandbased/binding-commands-to-triggers.html">link</a>
</li>
<li>As part of a compound command, using <a href="https://docs.wpilib.org/en/stable/docs/software/commandbased/command-groups.html">command groups</a> or <a href="https://docs.wpilib.org/en/stable/docs/software/commandbased/convenience-features.html">other convenience features</a>.</li>
</ul>
<p>If you find yourself scheduling a command any other way, that’s a clue that you’re structuring your code against the intended paradigm, and you should find a better way to do it.</p>","post_number":15,"post_type":1,"posts_count":34,"updated_at":"2022-08-10T04:58:58.288Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":14,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":1,"reads":95,"readers_count":94,"score":69.0,"yours":false,"topic_id":414034,"topic_slug":"schedule-a-command-without-calling-initialize","display_username":"Gavin Matthews","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"link_counts":[{"url":"https://docs.wpilib.org/en/stable/docs/software/commandbased/subsystems.html?highlight=default%20commands#setting-default-commands","internal":false,"reflection":false,"title":"Subsystems — FIRST Robotics Competition documentation","clicks":1},{"url":"https://docs.wpilib.org/en/stable/docs/software/commandbased/binding-commands-to-triggers.html","internal":false,"reflection":false,"title":"Binding Commands to Triggers — FIRST Robotics Competition documentation","clicks":0},{"url":"https://docs.wpilib.org/en/stable/docs/software/commandbased/structuring-command-based-project.html#robot","internal":false,"reflection":false,"title":"Structuring a Command-Based Robot Project — FIRST Robotics Competition documentation","clicks":0},{"url":"https://docs.wpilib.org/en/stable/docs/software/commandbased/command-groups.html","internal":false,"reflection":false,"title":"Command Groups — FIRST Robotics Competition documentation","clicks":0},{"url":"https://docs.wpilib.org/en/stable/docs/software/commandbased/convenience-features.html","internal":false,"reflection":false,"title":"Convenience Features — FIRST Robotics Competition documentation","clicks":0}],"read":true,"user_title":"","reply_to_user":{"id":49423,"username":"Gandagorn","name":"Elliot Scher","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/gandagorn/{size}/267112_2.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[{"id":2,"count":3}],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":38743,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"Programming mentor, Team 2102, RI, CSA (he/him)"},"post_url":"/t/schedule-a-command-without-calling-initialize/414034/15","custom_user_title":"Programming mentor, Team 2102, RI, CSA (he/him)","reactions":[{"id":"heart","type":"emoji","count":3}],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":3,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":true},{"id":3076498,"name":null,"username":"Starlight220","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/starlight220/{size}/150872_2.png","created_at":"2022-08-10T07:18:35.416Z","cooked":"<p>It sounds like you’re reimplementing a version of a sequential command group, and not in the most reliable way. I’d recommend using WPILib’s <code>SequentialCommandGroup</code>: it’s more tested, documented, and it’ll be easier for others to help if needed.</p>
<p>One important note: when using WPILib-provided command classes (especially the groups), <strong>do not override the lifecycle methods!!</strong> (<code>initialize</code>, <code>execute</code>, <code>isFinished</code>, <code>end</code>) – it causes issues that are difficult to debug, especially without knowledge about command internals. If you find that you need to override a lifecycle method, there’s probably a better way to structure things.<br>
I recommend using <a href="https://docs.wpilib.org/en/latest/docs/software/commandbased/convenience-features.html#inline-command-definitions" rel="noopener nofollow ugc">inline commands</a>, as opposed to writing old-style command classes – it’s much less verbose, and in my opinion more intuitive to structure.</p>
<p>Looking at code examples others here have linked is also a great way to learn.</p>
<p>Calling <code>schedule</code> manually is also somewhat of a code smell; see <a class="mention" href="/u/bovlb">@bovlb</a>’s comment. The <a href="https://docs.wpilib.org/en/latest/docs/software/commandbased/binding-commands-to-triggers.html" rel="noopener nofollow ugc">Trigger API</a> is expressive enough that it should cover almost any use case (and it’s getting enhanced for 2023).</p>
